-- Peru Stocks: Casa Grande, Maple, Rio Alto, Southern
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-06-13T21:20:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-13/peru-stocks-casa-grande-rio-alto-southern-copper.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of the market close.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  fell for a fourth session, losing
0.4 percent to 20,812.60. The MSCI All Peru Capped Index slid
0.3 percent to 2,712.83.  Maple Energy Plc (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas
producer with operations in Peru, fell 1.8 percent to $1.10
after crude slumped to an eight-month low in  New York .  Casa Grande  (CASAGRC1 PE), Peru’s largest sugar producer
and a unit of Gloria SA, fell for a third day, losing 1.5
percent to 13.50 soles after sugar declined in New York.  Rio Alto Mining Ltd. (RIO)  , a Canadian gold miner,
gained 1.9 percent to $4.25. The shares rallied after gold
advanced for a fourth session in New York, according to Angel
Alcala, a trader at Lima-based Juan Magot y Asociados SAB.  Southern Copper Corp. (SCCO)  , Peru’s biggest copper
producer, increased 1.4 percent to $29.86 as copper rose earlier
today in New York trading.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alexander Emery in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
